{
    "name": "Brasov Historical Center",
    "description": "The Old Town is the historic heart of the city, known for its well-preserved Saxon buildings, 15th-century fortifications and history museums. In Sfatului Square, which is bordered by cafes, there is also the Council House dating from the 15th century, as well as the imposing Gothic Black Church. Bars, restaurant terraces and nearby shops surround Republican Pedestrian Street, and cable car rides on Mount Tampa offer views of the city from the top.",
    "cityId": "612573579ccc5769789da0df",
    "imgSrc": "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
}

{
    "name": " Restaurant La Ceaun - Piata Sfatului",
    "description": "Traditional Romanian food, cooked slowly in a village outside the city and served fast in the Old Town Market. Due to the small number of seats, we are unable to take reservations. Should there be no table available, waiting times are generally up to 15-20 minutes. Looking forward to have you as our guests!",
    "cityId": "612573579ccc5769789da0df",
    "imgSrc": "https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-f/0f/65/8e/20/concert-in-the-old-market.jpg"
}

{
    "name": "Accommodation - Bradul Chalet",
    "description": "Idyllic location, beautiful and clean environment. Cosy, well priced guesthouse, great facilities, 12 km away from Bran Castle and 35 km away from Brasov. Perfect for travelers, families and groups. 35 km away from Brasov, settled in a marvellous mountain area, the Bradul Chalet can serve as the perfect base for making day trips to Dracula´s Castle, Brasov, Sighisoara, Sinaia, Predeal or Bucharest while enjoying the quiteness of a mountain village. If you have in mind a family holiday or a relaxing few days in nature, the village offers many possibilities of hiking, bike riding, guided animal watching tours. Bradul Chalet offers comfort, authenticity and tradition, harmoniously interlaced in a magical experience for the guests. The chalet is scenically located in the midst of nature and is just 12 km away from Bran, the well-known home of Count Dracula!",
    "cityId": "612573579ccc5769789da0df",
    "imgSrc": "https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/vr-splice-j/00/14/50/2f.jpg"
}

{
    "name": "Hotel Portrait Roma",
    "description": "Hospitality is an art and Portrait Roma has made it a masterpiece. In a new concept of bespoke tourism, we have transformed uniform luxury into spontaneous personalisation. Live a private mansion with the services of a 5 star hotel built around a city, a suite tailored to you and experiences crafted to your lifestyle. Let us make your stay in Rome a portrait of you. And let us make it better than perfect.",
    "cityId": "6125721b9ccc5769789da0b3",
    "imgSrc": "https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/17/28/4c/0a/lounge.jpg?w=1200&h=-1&s=1"
}

{
    "name": "Colosseum",
    "description": "The Colosseum is a historical and tourist monument located in the center of Rome visited by many tourists from around the world. It is probably the most impressive ruined building of the Roman Empire. The Colosseum was the largest building of its time and today is the largest ancient amphitheater that can be visited in Italy.",
    "cityId": "6125721b9ccc5769789da0b3",
    "imgSrc": "https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/attractions-splice-spp-720x480/06/71/2e/56.jpg"
}
